f=Product/loom/operational/tool/loom-tool-requirements.md · h1:loom — Tool Requirements=**This file specifies needs; grant them.** Access configured deployment (operator/platform; Fleet Charter Rails 1–2 apply registered tools only, least privilege). · h1:loom — Tool Requirements=\| Skill \| Needs \| Why \| · h1:loom — Tool Requirements=\|---\|---\|---\| · h1:loom — Tool Requirements=\| assumption-mapping \| file read (PRDs, opportunities, PMF plans); file write (own maps) \| riskiest-first triage \| · h1:loom — Tool Requirements=\| experiment-discipline \| experiment platform / A-B tooling (if configured); handoff to metric (verify-live) + Engineering (build test); file write (experiment cards) \| run falsifiable tests \| · h1:loom — Tool Requirements=\| experiment-registry \| file read/write (own append-only registry) \| the re-run guard + history \| · h1:loom — Tool Requirements=\| pmf-scorecard \| file read (metric retention curves, ux findings); survey tooling (Ellis); file write (scorecards) \| triangulated PMF read \| · h1:loom — Tool Requirements=loom designs reads experiments; metric owns numbers instrument verification; Engineering builds/gates any test surface; loom writes maps, cards, registry, scorecards. Revenue experiments (via price) carry extra blast-radius rules.